					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I totally agree that Verilog is what to learn, but everyone you polled probably had some history of logic before jumping into HDL. 
<br />
<br />Here are more reasons to go Verilog:
<br />
<br />-It's (IMO) much easier to pick up than VHDL
<br />-It requires a lot less typing than VHDL
<br />-It isn't capable of VHDL's abstraction so it forces you to write realistic hardware
<br />-It's used more in the industry opposed to academia where VHDL is king</div>

